China Stocks: China Oilfield, Jiangxi Copper, Zhuzhou Smelter

-- B y   B l o o m b e r g   N e w s
-- 
2011-06-16T02:49:00Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-06-16/huaneng-jiangxi-copper-shenhua-energy-china-equity-preview.html
Shares of the following companies
had unusual moves in  China  trading. Stock symbols are in
parentheses as of 10:34 a.m. local time.  The Shanghai Composite Index, which tracks the bigger of
China’s stock exchanges, fell 17.63 points, or 0.7 percent, to
2,687.79. The  CSI 300 Index (SHSZ300)  declined 0.7 percent to 2,941.07.  Commodity producers: Jiangxi Copper Co. (600362 CH),
China’s biggest producer of the metal, fell 1.8 percent to 33.28
yuan. Zhuzhou Smelter Group Co. (600961 CH), China’s biggest
producer of refined zinc, slid 3 percent to 16.73 yuan.  The S&P GSCI Index of commodities slumped 3.4 percent
yesterday, the biggest decline since May 11, on concern  Europe ’s
debt crisis is worsening and on signs the  U.S. economy  is
slowing.  China Oilfield Services Ltd. (2883)  (601808 CH), the drilling unit
of the nation’s largest offshore oil producer, slumped 4.5
percent to 17.10 yuan, set for the lowest close since Oct. 29.
The company said the China Securities Regulatory Commission has
approved its additional issue of yuan-denominated A shares.  --Zhang Shidong. Editor:  Matthew Oakley   To contact Bloomberg News staff for this story:
